epo": "T09_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the interest in `gwc`! \n\nThe `push` command isn't missing or removed — it's intentionally out of scope by design. The README documents this under the **\"Not supported\"** section:\n\n> Network operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`, `remote add`) are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.\n\n`gwc` is designed as a lightweight companion for local-only workflow shortcuts (currently `status-summary`, `branch-name`, and `clean-merged`), not as a full git replacement. For all network operations, plain `git` is the intended tool.\n\nClosing this as not-planned since it's working as designed."}, "id": "call_0c42732267744a128b883a02", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7192, "output_tokens": 558, "total_tokens": 7750, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6528}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 147}}}}]}}}
